headline: Inflation cooled slightly in December though it remains above Fed's target
summary: Consumer prices rose 0.3% in December from the prior month, the Labor Department said Tuesday, the same as in November.  Excluding the volatile food and energy categories, core prices rose 0.2%, also matching November's figure.  Increases at that pace, over time, would bring inflation closer to the Federal Reserve's target of 2%.
